@NODE History "History"

 @{b}History of Xtruder@{ub}

  Histories for 1.0 to 2.5 removed to save space.

  Version:

   @{" 3.0 " LINK VERS_30}
   @{" 3.1 " LINK VERS_31}
   @{" 3.2 " LINK VERS_32}
   @{" 3.3 " LINK VERS_33}
   @{" 3.4 " LINK VERS_34}
   @{" 3.5 " LINK VERS_35}
   @{" 3.6 " LINK VERS_36}
   @{" 3.7 " LINK VERS_37}
@ENDNODE

@NODE VERS_30 "Version 3.0  :  25.9.1996  :  182376 bytes"

 @{b}Changes@{ub}

  - First of all: Everything has changed. Do not expect anything to act as
    it did in earlier versions. Escpecially check your ARexx scripts :-)

  - Menu design almost completely changed.
  - On public screens Xtruder will just reside as a title bar.
  - File check GUI. Looks pretty damn nice if I may say so :)
  - File check GUI settings created so you can customize it to your
    likings.
  - When a string gadget with a popup gadget is active pressing cursor
    down will act as a click on the popup gadget.
  - Pressing cursor downp in a public screen/file/dir string gadget will
    cause a requester to pop up.
  - @{b}Corrupt path@{ub} changed to @{b}Recheck path@{ub}.
  - When Xtruder is quitting it will in case the settings have been
    changed ask if the settings should be saved. You also have the
    possibility to cancel and return to Xtruder.
  - Added miscellaneous menuitems for easy access to certain sections in
    this guide.
  - Virus Information window and accompanying functions completely
    rewritten.
  - Under OS3 the history window shows the file check in multiple colors
    instead of only using black.
  - Completely rewrote the report system. Reports created with older
    versions are obsolete and can not be used by Xtruder 3.
  - Created a comprehensive bootblock handling interface. Most bootblock
    routines rewritten. The bootblock is automatically shown when read and
    in both ASCII and hex format.
  - Bootblock ARexx commands removed.
  - It is now optional whether you want to suppress system messages during
    file checks or not.
  - Time check removed.
  - Checking a report at startup is not possible anymore. Use an ARexx
    script to do it :)
  - Online help is now available at more windows.

 @{b}Bug fixes@{ub}

  - Prespecified setttings could crash sometimes. @{fg highlight}Nicholas Clarke@{fg text}.
  - Could not show the window with the public screens list. @{fg highlight}Alex Holst@{fg text}.
@ENDNODE

@NODE VERS_31 "Version 3.1  :  10.10.1996  :  182408 bytes"

 @{b}Changes@{ub}

  - Included Swedish catalog translation by Tauno Pinni. Thanks Tauno!

 @{b}Bug fixes@{ub}

  - Corrected a few errors in the catalog translation routines. @{fg highlight}Jan Nielsen@{fg text}.
@ENDNODE

@NODE VERS_32 "Version 3.2  :  29.10.1996  :  182880 bytes"

 @{b}Changes@{ub}
 
  - Changed a few things in the @{b}System Information@{ub} window. Things
    which appear abnormal are now shown in white under OS3.x.

  - New version of filevirus.library included.

 @{b}Bug fixes@{ub}

  - Listing of known file viruses caused enforcer hits. @{fg highlight}Jan Andersen@{fg text}.
@ENDNODE

@NODE VERS_33 "Version 3.3  :  26.3.1997  :  183132 bytes"

 @{b}Changes@{ub}

  - When checking archives (using Internal 1) Xtruder now actually shows
    the tree structure of the archive during the checking the extracted
    files. Although this routine is not 100% perfect in some scenarios it
    will have to suffice for now :)
  - Now uses the system font for some requesters in the start. Looks
    nicer :)

 @{b}Bug fixes@{ub}

  - Could not extract archives if the @{b}archive extract path@{ub} included spaces
    in the name. @{fg highlight}Kenneth Lund Larsen@{fg text}.
  - When resizing the check window the path and file gadgets were not
    updated. Same bug occured with the bootblock interface window.
    @{fg highlight}Magnus Holmgren@{fg text}.
  - Forgot to save the coordinates of the main window used when on a
    public screen.
  - In the reports window the path was not remembered if it was typed in.
  - Implemented semaphores here and there to avoid race conditions.
  - Minor fixes here and there.
  - ARexx command @{b}Check vectors@{ub} was broken.

 @{b}Notes@{ub}

  - Added catalogs for German, French, Italian, Dutch, Norwegian, Finnish.
@ENDNODE

@NODE VERS_34 "Version 3.4  :  24.4.1997  :  183384 bytes"

 @{b}Changes@{ub}

  - It was brought to my attention that 'viruses' is the correct plural
    form of virus and not 'vira'. Changed hopefully everywhere. Including
    the ARexx command @{b}NUMBERVIRAFOUND@{ub} which is now called
    @{b}NUMBERVIRUSESFOUND@{ub}. Now if someone tells me I'm wrong I'm gonna smack
    them upside down the head ;)

 @{b}Bug fixes@{ub}

  - Removed enforcer hits that occured if the check window was closed
    while checking files. @{fg highlight}John Marchant@{fg text}.
  - The MSG_XTRUDERALREADYRUNNING string was not used with the
    localization feature. @{fg highlight}Mika Lundell@{fg text}.
  - If Xtruder was started twice the second copy would not quit properly.
    @{fg highlight}Mika Lundell@{fg text}.
  - Xtruder now finally works with Executive.
  - The system information showed the 5 exec vectors in decimal instead of
    hex. @{fg highlight}Mika Lundell@{fg text}.
  - Could not extract archives if the @{b}archive extract path@{ub} included spaces
    in the name. Should have been fixed in 3.3 :-/ @{fg highlight}Kenneth Lund Larsen@{fg text}.
  - Now specifies ENVARC: instead of ENV: in the save requester path when
    saving the settings under another filename. @{fg highlight}Kenneth Johnson@{fg text}.
@ENDNODE

@NODE VERS_35 "Version 3.5  :  18.6.1997  :  183700 bytes"

 @{b}Changes@{ub}

  - Filevirus.library now up to version 2.11.
    Added recognition for the:
      @{b}Visions@{ub} virus.
      @{b}Orb95@{ub} virus.

 @{b}Bug fixes@{ub}

  - Okay, I goofed up. The ARexx command @{b}NUMBERVIRAFOUND@{ub} has now
    actually been renamed to @{b}NUMBERVIRUSESFOUND@{ub}. Sorry!!

 @{b}Notes@{ub}

  - Corrected a lot of hyperlinks in this documentation. @{fg highlight}Jen Allen@{fg text}.
@ENDNODE

@NODE VERS_36 "Version 3.6  :  5.7.1997  :  183364 bytes"

 @{b}Changes@{ub}

  - Filevirus.library now up to version 2.12.
    Added recognition for the:
      @{b}Circle of Power 13@{ub} virus.
      @{b}Circle of Power 14@{ub} virus.

 @{b}Notes@{ub}

  - V3.5 seemed to cause loss of data for users who used fake keyfiles and
    they seem to be angry because of that. I fail to see why. You should
    be aware of unexpected behaviour when using "unauthorized" programs in
    conjunction with Xtruder (read the disclaimer).
    However, I have eliminated the risk of losing data.
@ENDNODE

@NODE VERS_37 "Version 3.7  :  28.8.1997  :  183124 bytes"

 @{b}Changes@{ub}

  - Filevirus.library now up to version 2.13.
    Improved recognition for the @{b}BGS-9@{ub} viruses.
    Improved recognition for the @{b}Alfons Ĺberg 2.0@{ub} virus. Recognition
    provided for both the 4EF9 linked file and the trojan itself.
    Added recognition for the:
      @{b}ADO! Installer@{ub} virus.
      @{b}AramDoll@{ub} link virus and removal code for it.
      @{b}Circle Of Power 15@{ub} virus.
      @{b}Circle Of Power 16@{ub} virus.
      @{b}VT Trojan@{ub} virus.
  - I have removed support for locale. It has been too much of a hazzle to
    keep updated.
  - @{b}Repair@{ub} and @{b}Show CRC@{ub} now remembers the last used path.

 @{b}Bug fixes@{ub}

  - @{b}Suppress system messages@{ub} was always loaded as unset. @{fg highlight}Robert W van der Hoek@{fg text}.
  - @{b}Repair@{ub} function would hang on data files.
@ENDNODE
